"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-paris-olympics-2024-tennis-schedule-uk-start-time-dates-b1172475.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Two months on from the French Open, all eyes are back on Paris as Roland Garros hosts thetennisevents at theOlympic Games.  Iga Swiatek and Carlos Alcaraz were victorious earlier this summer and they are the favourites to win gold for Poland and Spain respectively, with Alcaraz also well-fancied for a deep run in the men's doubles as his forms a heavyweight partnership with 14-time French Open champion Rafael Nadal.  Andy Murrayhasconfirmed he will retire from the sportafterParis 2024, and the Briton will be desperately hoping for a memorable farewell, having already twice been crowned Olympic champion.  Katie Boulter, Jack Draper and Heather Watson are among the other British athletes involved, while Novak Djokovic makes another bid, and almost certainly a final one, for Olympic gold.  (All times BST and provisional - order of play will be confirmed the evening before each day)  11:00:Men's singles first round  11:00:Women's singles first round  11:00:Men's doubles first round  11:00:Women's doubles first round  11:00:Men's singles first round  11:00:Women's singles first round  11:00:Men's doubles first round  11:00:Women's doubles first round  11:00:Men's singles second round  11:00:Women's singles second round  11:00:Men's doubles second round  11:00:Women's doubles second round  11:00:Mixed doubles first round  11:00:Men's singles second round  11:00:Women's singles third round  11:00:Men's doubles third round  11:00:Women's doubles second round  11:00:Mixed doubles first round  11:00:Men's singles third round  11:00:Women's singles quarter-finals  11:00:Men's doubles semi-finals  11:00:Wo